(67, 'string', 'content_en', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<h2>Positions Vacant</h2>\r\n<p>We are currently looking for permanent &amp; casual educators.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Job Positions</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Certificate III in Early Childhood Education &amp; Care</li>\r\n<li>Certificate III Trainee in Early Childhood Education &amp; Care</li>\r\n<li>Diploma in Early Childhood Education &amp; Care</li>\r\n<li>Early Childhood Teacher</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As a CIII or CIII Trainee, you will be responsible for contributing to a high quality early education and care program that supports children\'s learning and development and is aligned with the Early Years Learning Framework. Specifically, you will:</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with your team to develop an educational program that is appropriate to the individual needs and interests of the children</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work collaboratively to ensure the best outcomes for children and families</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist children to become confident and involved learners</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assess, reflect and share information with parents about the child\'s progress</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide children with a safe, welcoming and nurturing environment</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Essential Criteria CIII and Diploma</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A current paid working with children check number</li>\r\n<li>A Certificate III or Diploma level qualification in Children\'s Services as identified by the Australian Children\'s Education and Care Quality Authority</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of the National Quality Framework, National Quality Standards and EYLF</li>\r\n<li>An understanding of Child Protection and Mandatory Reporting</li>\r\n<li>Experience working with children aged 0-5 years</li>\r\n<li>Good communication, collaboration and organisational skills</li>\r\n<li>A passion for developing, planning and implementing an innovative educational program with a commitment to inclusive early childhood practice</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of the stages of physical, emotional, cognitive, social and cultural development of children.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of health, hygiene and the nutrition needs of children</li>\r\n<li>Experience in / or interest in additional needs / challenging behaviours</li>\r\n<li>A commitment to your own ongoing professional development in early childhood</li>\r\n<li>ACECQA approved qualifications and certificates in, or willingness to obtain; Child Protection, First Aid, Emergency Asthma Management, Emergency Anaphylaxis Management</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Essential Criteria CIII Trainee</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A current paid working with children check number</li>\r\n<li>Agreement to undertake an 18 month traineeship &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>\r\n<li>A friendly and energetic demeanor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>**</strong>Please note&nbsp;that by not addressing the selection criteria, this may affect your application and you may not be shortlisted.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;The successful candidate/s will be required to successfully complete a National Criminal History Record Check, have a current employee Working with Children Check, sign a Health Declaration, and present evidence of the right to Work in Australia.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Position Terms:</strong> Permanent Full Time- Shifts between 7.45am and 5.15pm, Monday to Friday. The service closes for 2 weeks over the Christmas period.</p>\r\n<p>Please complete the attached application document in full and email it with your resume to assistant.director@gloucesterpreschool.com.au&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Application for Employment Form\" href=\"uploads/pdf/employment/220802-Application_for_Employment_Form.pdf\">220802-Application_for_Employment_Form</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Early Childhood Teacher position</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Join Gloucester Preschool &amp; Early Years Learning Centre as an ECT<br /> <br /> Being an Early Childhood Teacher at Gloucester Preschool &amp; Early Years Learning Centre means being a part of an exceeding team of educators. You will have a voice and the opportunity to make decisions and develop a learning program that suits the families and their children in our community. For the right candidate, full time position is available.</p>\r\n<p>Only 2.5 hours from Sydney, 1.5 hours from Newcastle and located on the beautiful Barrington Coast, you&rsquo;ll also have a great place to work, incredible colleagues, and&nbsp;benefits&nbsp;that include:</p>\r\n<p>Remumeration: Enterprises Agreement with above award wages from $39-$63 depending on experience. Childcare discounts &amp; annual bonuses included. <br />Professionalism: A professional learning community where your excellence is celebrated, and success is supported with mentoring, additional programming, planning, professional meeting time &amp; a EAP.<br />Voice and Influence: As an Early Childhood Teacher at Gloucester Preschool &amp; Early Years Learning Centre, you\'ll have a say in shaping learning programs.<br />Collaboration: Work with professional Educators and Teachers, sharing best practices and learning from each other with paid meeting time for room meetings, leadership meetings and whole service meetings.<br />Quality Learning Environments: Award winning learning environments with well-resourced spaces for children and Teachers.<br />Skills Enhancement: Paid first aid courses and other professional development annually.<br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Centre<br />Gloucester Preschool &amp; Early Years Learning Centre is on Worimi &amp; Biripi Country on the Mid North Coast. It is a community based not-for-profit service providing preschool. Long day care and support playgroup sessions. Rated as exceeding we are licenced for 85 children and currently operate with a daily capacity of 58 children. The service has been established for 50 years and caters for children aged 0 to 5 years. We are passionate about creating the very best learning environments and the highest quality early learning programs.</p>\r\n<p>Our philosophy focuses on the rights of the child, collaboration with families &amp; the local community. Our pedagogy focuses on nature, environmental sustainability, risky play and positive social and emotional skill development. We use project books to inspire creative engagement in learning, provoke imaginative, curiosity and a sense of wonder.</p>\r\n<p>The Centre has exceptional indoor and outdoor environments that are spacious and focus on nature elements that support the holistic development of children. We have four indoor learning spaces, and 3 outdoor learning environments. Each room is filled with quality educational resources for the best in play-based learning. Every child is supported to develop a lifelong love of learning.<br /> <br /> The Role&nbsp;<br /> The role requires a creative and passionate Early Childhood Teacher to work as an active team member in providing high quality education and care. This is a great opportunity for early childhood professionals who are passionate about early childhood education to be involved with a supportive professional team and with likeminded educators who believe in children and the importance of Early Childhood and the value it adds to children\'s lives.</p>\r\n<p>Key Selection Criteria</p>\r\n<p>ACECQA recognised Degree in Early Childhood Teaching<br />Current NESA Teacher&rsquo;s Accreditation<br />Current First Aid Training HLTAID012<br />Child Protection &ndash; CHCPRT001 or CHCPRT025<br />Valid Working with Children&rsquo;s Check</p>\r\n<p><br />Experience</p>\r\n<p>Excellent understanding and working knowledge of the National Quality Framework, which includes National Regulations, National Quality Standards (NQS), and the Early Years Learning Framework (EYLF)<br />Demonstrated experience in curriculum development &amp; documenting children&rsquo;s learning.<br />Previous experience working in the early childhood sector (desirable)<br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Capabilities</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Excellent written and verbal communication skills.<br />Ability to work collaboratively and cooperatively in a team environment.<br />A commitment to continuous improvement and ongoing professional learning.<br />Commitment to inclusion and equity and cultural competency.<br />Commitment to nature pedagogy and sustainability.<br />Commitment to embedding Aboriginal Torres Strait Islander culture into the program.<br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Desirable skills</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with Xplor</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MS Teams</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cloud server systems</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Apply now to join Gloucester Preschool &amp; Early Years Learning Centre or email assistant.director@gloucesterpreschool.com.au for more information.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2024-05-15 08:23:23'),
