(86, 2, 0, '<p>Research shows us that the quality of provision and children\'s outcomes almost never exceeds the quality of leadership and management. &ldquo;&hellip;. there is no doubt that effective leadership and appropriate training for the leadership role is an increasingly important element in providing high-quality provision for the early years&rdquo; Siraj-Blatchford 7 Manni 2007.</p>\r\n<p>This goal will support &amp; enhance our Early Childhood Teacher\'s current leadership skills as well as develop the emerging leadership skills of our two new Diploma Trainee Room Leaders.</p>\r\n<p>Outcomes for the QIP</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A collaborative leadership team within the organisation.</li>\r\n<li>A collective shared vision that is reflective of the services philosophy and expectations.</li>\r\n<li>Efffective leaders promote positive organisational culture and builds a professional learning community.</li>\r\n<li>Distributed leadership within the organisation.</li>\r\n<li>Effective communication skills.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Short Term Strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Understand Room Leader goals and responsibilities.</li>\r\n<li>Understand Siraj-Blatchford &amp; L Manni, 10 categories of &lsquo;effective leadership practice&rsquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Build a culture of safe &amp; positive reflective practice for the leadership team</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Long Term Strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A community of leaders committed to building practice and skills by sharing ideas and issues with each other.</li>\r\n<li>Professional relationships that are based on a shared understanding enabling formal &amp; informal opportunities to meet to share ideas, discuss common issues and concerns and support each other to develop professional competence.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL),
(86, 13, 0, '11-07-2023', NULL),
(86, 20, 0, '2023-No.1-QIP-Leadership.pdf', NULL),
(87, 2, 0, '<p>The Early Years Learning Framework has been updated for use starting 2023. The original framework will remain in operation alongside this in 2023. Educator will need to understand the changes over the year so that they can embed them by 2024.</p>\r\n<p>Outcomes</p>\r\n<p>The main differences you will see are a stronger connection between&nbsp;the frameworks and the National Quality Standard in areas such as&nbsp;sustainability, theoretical approaches, critical reflection, the importance of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander ways of being, knowing and doing, inclusion and the addition of three new principles.&nbsp;Using the EYLF to drive curriculum decisions.</p>\r\n<p>Short term Strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All staff have access to new document.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Identify the key areas of change</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Long term Strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Embedded curriculum of EYLF</li>\r\n<li>Educators have the confidence to verbally explain how the EYLF supports &amp; guides their pedagogy.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(87, 13, 0, '22-07-2023', NULL),
(87, 20, 0, '2023_No.2_QIP_EYLF_changes.pdf', NULL),
(88, 2, 0, '<p>Educators &amp; staff working in the Early Childhood Professional are under increasing pressures from workload, expectations, time pressures and challenging student behaviour. This can affect their job satisfaction, mental health and relationships with children, colleagues &amp; community.</p>\r\n<p>Outcomes</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reducing &amp; managing employees stress levels</li>\r\n<li>Maintaining positive social interactions</li>\r\n<li>Empowered to ask for help or support when needed</li>\r\n<li>Maintaining a supportive culture at our service</li>\r\n<li>Taking responsibility for your mental health.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Short term strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Be You training.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Policy development&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Be You Wellbeing Plan for educators&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Long term strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Positive culture of wellbeing &amp; mental health&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Staff have skills &amp; strategies embedded for positive wellbeing.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Positive work life balance&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(88, 13, 0, '22-07-2023', NULL),
(88, 20, 0, '2023_Staff_Wellbeing26.7.2023.pdf', NULL),
(89, 2, 0, '<p>Educators can be challenged to support children who display behaviours that do not fit into our cultural expectations. This can increase educators&rsquo; workload, stress and ability to develop positive relationships with children.&nbsp; Different cultural &amp; professional knowledge &amp; beliefs reflect inconsistent strategies been used to support children in the service.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Outcomes</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A foundational understanding of the Conscious Discipline Brain State Model and how to create safe, connected and problem-solving environments that allow adults and children to function in their optimal brain state.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Consistency in philosophical understanding of children&rsquo;s behavior&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Consistent pedagogy approach in supporting children&rsquo;s social &amp; emotional development.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Educators&rsquo; that feel competent and supported in working in the classrooms with children.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Short term Strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Have all educators enrolled in the Conscious Discipline course&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Long Term Strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Knowledge &amp; skills on conscious discipline is embedded in educators&rsquo; practices.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Educators support the continuous flow of knowledge to new educators as they join our team.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Educators engage in a lifelong journey of developing, reflecting &amp; implementing conscious discipline teaching strategies.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL),
(89, 13, 0, '22-07-2023', NULL),
(89, 20, 0, '2023_No4_Conscious_Discipline.docx.pdf', NULL),
(90, 2, 0, '<p>The service has a large team and unique outdoor learning environment. Many educators have differing views about the setup, maintenance and their roles and responsibilities in this environment.</p>\r\n<p>Outcomes</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The outdoor learning environment philosophy supports the service philosophy.</li>\r\n<li>The philosophy will guide and inform the services&rsquo; community from educators, children, parents, and the wider community to understand the &lsquo;why&rsquo; behind the uniqueness of our outdoors learning environment and how it is used to support children&rsquo;s development, sustainability, and our local natural biodiversity. &nbsp;The philosophy will support our work with children, their families and each other. It is the combination of our beliefs, values and hopes for the outdoor educational program that we provide and its outcomes.</li>\r\n<li>The philosophy will support our pedagogy.</li>\r\n<li>Goals and responsibility will be developed for each keys learning area.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Short Term Strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Survey educators</li>\r\n<li>Survey families</li>\r\n<li>Draft philosophy and gather feedback</li>\r\n<li>Collaborate with educator on pedagogy, goals &amp; expectations.</li>\r\n<li>Draft and finalise document</li>\r\n<li>Add document to orientation package</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Long Term Strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Add philosophy to new webpage</li>\r\n<li>Write supportive articles for webpage.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL),
(90, 13, 0, '24-07-2023', NULL),
(90, 20, 0, 'Plan_6 2021_Outdoor_Learning_Environment_Philosophy.pdf', NULL),
(91, 2, 0, '<p>To manage pests in our service&rsquo;s indoor &amp; outdoor environments while understanding their role within a balanced natural environment.</p>\r\n<p>To manage perceived pests while supporting minimal toxic chemical use and the health &amp; safety of staff, children &amp; visitors to our service. Connected to Sustainability Project Book pg 29, 10/3/2022</p>\r\n<p>Outcomes</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Staff &amp; children are educated and supported in their knowledge to identify insects, arachnids (spiders), gastropods (slugs &amp; snails), hymenopters (wasps, bees &amp; ants), lepidoptera (moths, butterflies in all stages of development), reptiles, snakes, birds &amp; other rodents that may live or be present from time to time in our indoor &amp; outdoor environments.</li>\r\n<li>Their life cycles, habits and risks to humans &amp; property are understood so controls and management can be practiced in an environmentally sustainable way.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Short Term Strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Identify what staff, children &amp; families consider are pests in our environment.</li>\r\n<li>Understand their risks to the health &amp; wellbeing of the humans, resources, flora &amp; fauna.</li>\r\n<li>Understand how to manage the risk using natural, low toxic or toxic chemicals.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Long Term Strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Design a resource to support the identification of pest risks in our indoor &amp; outdoor environments.</li>\r\n<li>Design a risk assessment &amp; matrix to support management &amp; control measures of risks.</li>\r\n<li>Ongoing support &amp; education in this area as new staff, committees &amp; families are involved with our organisation.</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(91, 13, 0, '24-07-2023', NULL),
(91, 20, 0, 'Plan_2022_No.1_Risk_assessment_for_Pest_Managment_Plan.pdf', NULL),
(92, 2, 0, '<p>Educators feel challenged by the workload completing individual documentation for all children as well as programming and planning for the classroom and outdoor learning environments. Educators feel some documentation is unnecessary and not significant to children.</p>\r\n<p>Outcomes</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Documentation is meaningful and significant to children&rsquo;s individual learning journey</li>\r\n<li>Workload for educators is reduced</li>\r\n<li>Increased involvement/input from families</li>\r\n<li>Clear links between documentation and children&rsquo;s goals</li>\r\n<li>Clear planning cycle</li>\r\n<li>Documentation will continue to support our philosophy, EYLF &amp; NQS</li>\r\n<li>Quality and quantity of documentation is consistent across the service</li>\r\n<li>Documentation is differentiated to suit different age groups</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Short Term Strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Discussions with educators</li>\r\n<li>Research alternatives to current documentation</li>\r\n<li>Survey to families</li>\r\n<li>Differentiate documentation for age groups</li>\r\n<li>Identify possible changes</li>\r\n<li>Trial changes and review</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Long Term Strategies</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Identify best quality outcomes and implement changes</li>\r\n<li>Update Orientation document</li>\r\n<li>Update documentation overviews in staff manual</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL),
(92, 13, 0, '24-07-2023', NULL),
(92, 20, 0, '2022_No.2_QIP_Documention.pdf', NULL);
